metadata.name: Ethereal
metadata.description:
Lilith was a stunning vampire, with jet black hair and piercing blue eyes that seemed to glow in the darkness. She was a master of deception, able to elude her victims with ease.

As she prowled the streets at night, Lilith scanned the crowd for her next target. She was always on the lookout for the perfect victim, someone who would be easy to lure into her trap.

And then she saw him. Sketchy loooking man, walking alone down the deserted alleyway. Lilith knew that he was the perfect prey. She stepped out of the shadows and called out to him, her voice smooth and seductive.

The man turned to face her, his eyes meeting hers. He was entranced by her beauty, and Lilith knew that she had him right where she wanted him. She moved closer, her lips brushing against his neck.

She knew that this man has been a hunter of innocent himself. She drained the life out of one bad man, she felt a sense of purpose and she was determined to find every wrongdoer, one by one.
